column7:
Kindergarten: District 1 schools give priority to two groups of applicants. The percentage of seats prioritized for each group is based on the applicant pool and changes each year: Group 1. Applicants who are eligible for free or reduced price lunch (based on family income), live in temporary housing, or are English Language Learners. For the 2020-21 School Year, this group was prioritized for 67% of seats. Group 2. Students who do not fall into any of the above categories. For the 2020-21 School Year, this group was prioritized for 33% of seats.
